"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:4.8.4\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">4.8.4</span> Bier, coffin</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">אֲרוֹן</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(’aron)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:26\">GEN 50:26</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מִטָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(mitah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:31\">2SA 3:31</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">σορός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(soros)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:14\">LUK 7:14</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0470_coffin.jpg\" alt=\"Stone coffins or ossuaries in the garden of Dominus Flevit on the Mount of Olives\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Stone coffins or ossuaries in the garden of Dominus Flevit on the Mount of Olives (© Deror Avi, CC BY-SA 3.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>The bier was a board on which a body was carried to its place of burial, and the coffin was a box in which a body was placed for burial.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:26\">GEN 50:26</a> the Hebrew word <em>’aron</em> is literally “box,” but it means “coffin” in this context.</p>\n<p>In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:31\">2SA 3:31</a> the Hebrew word <em>mitah</em> is literally “bed.” The context, however, makes it clear that the object is serving as a bier or, less likely, a coffin.</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:14\">LUK 7:14</a>: In this verse some translations render the Greek word <em>soros</em> as “coffin” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr>). This word can also refer to a “bier,” and that is its more probable meaning here. In some languages it may be necessary to use a descriptive expression, for example, “board on which the body was being carried” or “box in which the body lay.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
